Algorithm
Define the initial state and goal state.
Calculate the heuristic value (Manhattan Distance).
Generate all possible moves of the blank tile.
Choose the node with the minimum cost:
f(n) = g(n) + h(n)
Repeat until the goal state is reached.
Print the solution path.

